"{\"uid\": \"dailycaller.com-2024-07-26-daily-caller-columnist-mary-rooke-slams-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"text\": \"(Photo by David Ramos/Getty Images)  Daily Caller columnist Mary Rooke criticized the Olympics opening ceremony during a Friday appearance on \\\"Frontline\\\" with host Carl Higbie.  In a scathing critique of the 2024Olympicsopening ceremony, Rooke voiced concerns that the event represented a broader cultural shift away from Western traditionalvalues. Rooke's commentary highlighted what she perceives to be a deliberate exclusion ofChristiansand traditionalists from the cultural narrative.  You all can catch me on@CarlHigbieFrontline on@NEWSMAXtonight at 5:25 pm ET!@DailyCallerpic.twitter.com/VHlZdcqcmp  - Mary Rooke (@MaryRooke_)July 26, 2024    \\\"Yeah, you are literally watching the fall of the West right now. That's what we are watching. It's like it's the minority standing up and going, 'Christians, traditionalists, you are not welcome here,'\\\" Rooke told Higbie. \\\"We do not want anything to do with you. Whenever you take something like the Lord's Supper and you bastardize it and put in a bunch of drag queens -\\u00a0and the way they were moving too was just so hilarious.\\\"  The sentiments Rooke expresses in the interview are echoed by a number of Twitter posts responding to the ceremony.(RELATED: 'Coordinated' Arson Attack Throws Wrench In Opening Of Paris Olympic Games)  Wtf is going on at the Olympics opening ceremony?pic.twitter.com/rWIjH8ZVwP  - Harrison Faulkner (@Harry__Faulkner)July 26, 2024    Shout out to the Paris Olympics#OpeningCeremonyfor me having to explain to my children what a M\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois is.pic.twitter.com/ivMhpzuEh4  - Vance Lucas (@vlucas)July 26, 2024    The 2024 Olympic Games kicked off Friday evening with a lavish riverside extravaganza, featuring an armada of boats transporting athletes down the Seine,accordingto The Guardian. The spectacle included dancers suspended from tall poles, drag queens strutting on bridges and the Olympic rings illuminating the Eiffel Tower.  The Vaticanissueda shortstatementto journalists in French on Aug. 3 saying it \\\"was saddened by certain scenes at the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic Games and cannot but join the voices raised in recent days to deplore the offense done to many Christians and believers of other religions.\\\"  In response to the July 26 Paris Olympics opening ceremony that mocked the Last Supper, the Vatican on Saturday issued a statement denouncing the scene.#Olympics#OlympicGames#Paris2024https://t.co/nQUK7NoHue  - Catholic News Agency (@cnalive)August 3, 2024    TRENDING  \\u00a92025 The Daily Caller, Inc.  The Daily Caller | 1775 Eye Street NW | Suite 1150-290 | Washington, DC 20006\"}"